I go back to MU in a week. So here's my schedule if anyone is interested in getting together before I leave.

Sunday: I dont think anything is planned...if there is it's at night.
Monday: possibly out to walmart for some more shopping. that night my cousins are coming over for a sleepover.
Tuesday: Knoebels with the family.
Wednesday: open.
Thursday: open.
Friday: day is open, night I'm going to the fireworks with eric.&nbsp;
Saturday: I leave. yay!

Mom, dad, and amanda want to go out to ice cream and mini golf as a family one of those nights, not sure if it'll be sunday, wednesday or thursday. And I still have to find some time to pack.&nbsp;

Other than that, I'm free.&nbsp;

So...yeah.

I'm going to take a power nap then eat dinner, then go hang out with Eric.&nbsp;
&lt;3

They say don't dwell on the past. So I won't.&nbsp;
But man, I read through old journal entries looking for some advice for a friend.&nbsp;
I came across conversations with Hardcore. Where he's asking who I was going to do next.&nbsp;
One conversation Hardcore, Ben, Tim, and Adam were all telling me I was a liar when I said I have never been fingered. ...because they would know what happens to my body...
Another conversation (along with others) was about Eric and I...and Ben was telling me I needed to learn that he never loved me and I never loved him.

No wonder I was a wreck in high school. I had no confidence to begin with. I was depressed. And I had people left and right nagging me about my life which was none of their business. Good thing I'm not as weak as I was then. I've learned to stand up for myself. (I know, it's about time right?).
I'm not bringing up the past to start anything. I really could care less...it happened, it's over with...and I would never had remembered it if I hadn't been peering through old entries. I don't hold grudges that badly.&nbsp;

It's amazing how much I've changed. I know no one really cares. But I'm going to write this anyways lol. I was writing an email to a friend of mine who is falling into depression. It's a scary thing to be in and very few people understand how far deep I was into it all. It's the worst form of torture. But it was weird me being the one giving someone else the advice people had given me. Like how people can be assholes but they only get to you if you let them. To dismiss and let go. And most importantly: Life Goes On.&nbsp;

Even though old entries like the ones I came across piss me off (not as badly as they did then) I still would like to thank those people I put through hell. (although at times you did just as much to me). Looking back you guys really were just trying to help me and look out for me. It's just hard to see that when all you see is your world falling apart past the tears you're constantly fighting back.&nbsp;

Most of us don't keep in touch anymore. I can't even remember when the whole gang was together. And who knows...we probably all will never be together again. So if you were close to me in some degree in high school and you're reading this: Thank you. Every inch of support ...even the stuff that pissed me off and made me cry even more... really helped me get through it all and learn how to stand up for myself. I appreciate it. And I hope the best for all of you.&nbsp;

I guess I should finish up moving my junk around. I cleaned out my room and organized my junk. Just have a little bit more to take care of. I want to get it all done tonight. Tomorrow I'm going to Camp Lackawanna to spend the night with Eric. Coming back to the towanda/wysox area friday. Going to Body Electric. Maybe a movie. Spending the night with him. Then coming home in the morning. And saturday I have plans with family. So hopefully I can get the rest of this stuff cleaned up before I leave tomorrow.&nbsp;

And for those of you rolling your eyes or picking up your jaw that just dropped to the floor: Don't worry. I know to watch myself around him. Believe me...after how many heartaches and harsh words? I'd be the one to know when I need to get out of a situation. We're not going back out. We just started talking mid April when I unblocked him after about 5 months. We've talked a lot about our past. And we want to just spend some quality friendship time together.&nbsp;
...oh what am I doing? I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU THINK!!!
hahaha.&nbsp;


Have a good summer everyone!

Mansfield University presents Beauty and the Beast....
February 22nd, 23rd, and 24th at 8:00 pm. February 25th at 2:00 pm.
Adults: $12. Students/Seniors: $10.&nbsp;

Yes..the show is this upcoming thursday-sunday. I'm really excited but also really concerned. It's going to be hectic the next few days. Tonight is a full run through with costumes, hair, make up, orchestra for the first time, and lighting for the first time. I also have tvclub tonight at 4:30 (rehersal at 7:30..have to be there early of course). And I have class at 9, 1, 2, and 3. I hate mondays.&nbsp;

Just thought I'd share the dates and times and prices.&nbsp;
I'm a sexy big ass plate (seriously...our outfits are itty bitty). and a townsperson in Belle and the Mob Scene.&nbsp;
So you should come see it. It's gonna be good.&nbsp;

&lt;3

alright. new name has been made.&nbsp;
i probably won't write in this one much anymore, if at all.&nbsp;
so, a well-deserved: goodbye.

Do you ever wonder if college is really where you are supposed to be? I have no idea what I'm doing here. I don't know where I'm going with my major and minor. I really don't know anymore. Not as if I had a huge idea to begin with. I mean, I think what I'm in now is good for me, but I just don't know what is going to result from having my major and minor what they are.&nbsp;
I might've shrunk some pants. I'm not getting fatter so it must be that. Although last night I came to a decision that I'm fuckin hot and I don't care what anyone else says otherwise.&nbsp;
A lot of things are falling apart out here. But that stuff I will save for my friends only entry. Because honestly, I dont even know why I have this lj. The people that are on my 'friends list'...most of them don't keep in touch anymore. No matter how hard I try to leave messages or im them, I get nothing in return. I guess it sums up how my friendships have been. Who knows, maybe they did a better job at covering up not liking me than adam the asshole did. Seems to be the trend.&nbsp;
Fuck people and relationships. I dont need to be loved or cared about...I'm fine on my own.&nbsp;
Don't you hate it when you should be doing a million things and you aren't doing one of them? I should be up in the studio editing. But then I decided getting caught up while i have some free time this week is more important. So I got something done online. Now here I sit, wasting time writing to all of you who probably stopped reading after the first line.&nbsp;
Yep. Good stuff.&nbsp;
If you are on my friends only list, up next: more insightful stuff that you just might be interested in reading because you care that much about me. (maybe).&nbsp;

great response.

I absotutely hate the feeling of numbness in my mouth. My last cavity has been taken care of and the novicane is wearing off. Darn those braces.
Last night I was a rebel and stayed up till 1 in the morning. I heart late night chats and my guy friends.&nbsp;
Alex called me twice this morning. I laughed for an hour.
I need to finish packing tonight. And figure out why my printer wont print.&nbsp;
Fireworks in Monroeton tomorrow night. I'm going since I'm missing Riverfest. Not sure how I'm getting there...considering my cars muffler is shot. But I'm goin. lol.
I hate being poor. I have $7.64 in my account.&nbsp;
Tomorrow marks 10 months for alex and i.&nbsp;
I love looking through old pictures. I found some from the beach sophomore year. Back before Tims hair went on a growing spree. Back when I was still in depression. Back before Christa started loosing weight and looking even more beautiful than she already did. Back when I was still really good friends with people I can't stand anymore.&nbsp;
haha. Speaking of people I can't stand...I had a funny dream the other night. I think it proves I need to let go of some inner anger. lol. I'd tell you about it but you'd think I was crazy.
Oh shucks. I don't want to get back to packing.&nbsp;
I love listening to the dentist and his assistant talk while they are working on my teeth. You never know what you'll learn.
Had a good time last night with Peg even though my car decided to be flamboiant.&nbsp;
Dinner was only 7 dollars because the lady messed up our order. Yay cheap food.&nbsp;

So the main reason that I'm writing this is not to fill you with useless knowledge of my life but to let you know that I'm going to (not change my screen name haha) and start putting this on friends only. There's only a few people that I know of that might still read this. And I don't care to tell the whole world about my life anymore. So...I know I'm friending a few people and I'm sure you know who you are...but if you want to be friended and fill your mind with useless knowledge of my life then please respond. I'm not a mind reader.

Ummm. Yeah. I guess I should see why my printer decided to just stop working.

Band camp starts saturday...what insane group memorizes 31 songs and learns the whole field show in six days? we do...
I love the last thing on the list of what you should bring to camp: *excitement, energy, and a positive attitude!!!*

4 days left of summer.&nbsp;
